<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07926</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROMOTING SAFE AND RESPONSIBLE USE OF MODERN BIOTECHNOLOGY, ESTABLISHING THE BIOTECHNOLOGY AUTHORITY OF THE PHILIPPINES FOR THIS PURPOSE AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREOF</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to support safe and responsible use of modern biotechnology for the development of bio-based industries in agriculture, agroforestry, food processing, human health and medicine, and procession of high value commercial products;,Defines the following terms as used in this Act:
Genetically Modified Organism (GMO) refers to an organism whose genetic material has been altered through genetic engineering;
Modern Biotechnology refers to techniques for modifying genomes for the production of new bio-based products; Proposes to abolish the National Committee on Biosafety of the Philippines (NCBP) and other modern biotech regulatory bodies and their functions shall be absorbed by the BioAP.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GARIN, SHARON S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-07-18</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2018-09-18)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>